{"word":"σύμπλους","slug":"σύμπλους","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σύμπλους</b></el> <el>(σύμπλους, ουν,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:συμπλέω'><el>συμπλέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>sailing with</i> one in a <i>ship, a shipmate</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> of ships, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>a partner</i> or <i>comrade in</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}